After this change, you should see the curved arc instead of the straight line.

You now have control over **longest vs shortest distance**, with longest as the default.

### 1) Distance functions

In `geoCal.ts`:

- **Shortest distance (existing)** – still the haversine / great‑circle shortest arc:

```1:12:app/lib/geoCal.ts
/**
 * Haversine Distance (km) - always returns the shortest great-circle distance
 * between two points on the sphere.
 */
export function calculateDistance(
  lat1: number,
  lon1: number,
  lat2: number,
  lon2: number
): number {
  const R = 6371; // Earth radius in km
  ...
}
```

- **Longest distance (new)** – complementary arc around the globe:

```30:41:app/lib/geoCal.ts
/**
 * Longest great-circle distance (km) between two points.
 * This is the complementary arc to the shortest distance around the globe.
 */
export function calculateLongestDistance(
  lat1: number,
  lon1: number,
  lat2: number,
  lon2: number
): number {
  const R = 6371; // Earth radius in km
  const shortest = calculateDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2);
  const circumference = 2 * Math.PI * R;
  return circumference - shortest;
}
```

### 2) How the API chooses which distance to use

In `app/api/flight/route.ts`:

- **Query param**: `distanceType=longest|shortest`
  - Default is **`longest`** (if you omit it or send something else).

```20:24:app/api/flight/route.ts
  // Path style: "straight" = straight line, "curved" = Bézier arc (map shape)
  const pathStyleParam = searchParams.get("pathStyle");
  // Distance type: "longest" (default) or "shortest" for the numeric distance
  const distanceTypeParam = searchParams.get("distanceType");
```

- **Selection logic & duration**:

```46:62:app/api/flight/route.ts
  /* ===========================
     DISTANCE + BEARING
  =========================== */

  const distanceType =
    distanceTypeParam === "shortest" ? "shortest" : "longest";

  const shortestDistance = calculateDistance(
    fromAirport.lat,
    fromAirport.lng,
    toAirport.lat,
    toAirport.lng
  );

  const longestDistance = calculateLongestDistance(
    fromAirport.lat,
    fromAirport.lng,
    toAirport.lat,
    toAirport.lng
  );

  const distance =
    distanceType === "shortest" ? shortestDistance : longestDistance;

  const bearing = calculateBearing(
    fromAirport.lat,
    fromAirport.lng,
    toAirport.lat,
    toAirport.lng
  );

  const averageSpeed = 850;
  const durationHours = shortestDistance / averageSpeed;
```

- **Response uses the selected distance**:

```116:121:app/api/flight/route.ts
  return NextResponse.json({
    from: fromAirport,
    to: toAirport,
    distance: distance.toFixed(2),
    bearing: bearing.toFixed(2),
    durationHours: durationHours.toFixed(2),
    ...
  });
```

> Note: `durationHours` and arrival time still use the **shortest** distance (realistic flight), while `distance` returned can be longest or shortest depending on `distanceType`.

### 3) Path on the map (still independent)

- Path shape is controlled by **`pathStyle`**:
  - Default / `pathStyle=straight` → straight line via `generateStraightLinePath`.
  - `pathStyle=curved` → curved Bézier arc via `generateCurvedBezierPath`.

```82:93:app/api/flight/route.ts
  const pathStyle = pathStyleParam === "curved" ? "curved" : "straight";

  const path =
    pathStyle === "straight"
      ? generateStraightLinePath(
          fromAirport.lat,
          fromAirport.lng,
          toAirport.lat,
          toAirport.lng
        )
      : generateCurvedBezierPath(
          fromAirport.lat,
          fromAirport.lng,
          toAirport.lat,
          toAirport.lng,
          50,
          0.3
        );
```

### 4) How you use it

- **Default (longest distance, straight line)** – no extra params:

```text
/api/flight?from=JFK&to=SYD&dt=...
```

- **Shortest distance instead**:

```text
/api/flight?from=JFK&to=SYD&dt=...&distanceType=shortest
```

- **Combine with curved path visually** (if you want):

```text
/api/flight?from=JFK&to=SYD&dt=...&distanceType=shortest&pathStyle=curved
```

Right now your UI still calls the endpoint without extra params, so it shows **longest distance by default** and a **straight line** path; when you want the shortest distance you just add `distanceType=shortest` to the API call (or I can wire a toggle in the frontend for you).

### What I implemented

#### 1) Backend: sun timeline along the flight

In `sunCal.ts` I added a per-segment sun timeline and exposed it in the flight sun data:

```12:18:app/lib/sunCal.ts
export interface SunTimelinePoint {
  lat: number;
  lng: number;
  time: Date;
  sun: SunPosition;
  bearing: number;
}

export interface FlightSunData {
  departureSun: SunPosition;
  arrivalSun: SunPosition;
  scenicSide: "left" | "right" | "both" | "none";
  sunriseTime: Date | null;
  sunsetTime: Date | null;
  timeline: SunTimelinePoint[];
}
```

Inside `calculateFlightSunData`:

- I now build both a `timeline` (all segments) and `visibleSunPositions` (used for scenic side):

```186:226:app/lib/sunCal.ts
  const path = generateStraightPath(
    departureLat,
    departureLng,
    arrivalLat,
    arrivalLng,
    20
  );

  const timeline: SunTimelinePoint[] = [];
  const visibleSunPositions: {
    azimuth: number;
    altitude: number;
    bearing: number;
  }[] = [];

  for (let i = 0; i < path.length - 1; i++) {
    const current = path[i];
    const next = path[i + 1];

    const progress = i / (path.length - 1);

    const currentTime = new Date(
      departureTime.getTime() +
        flightDurationHours * progress * 60 * 60 * 1000
    );

    const sunPos = getSunPosition(currentTime, current.lat, current.lng);
    const bearing = calculateBearing(
      current.lat,
      current.lng,
      next.lat,
      next.lng
    );

    timeline.push({
      lat: current.lat,
      lng: current.lng,
      time: currentTime,
      sun: sunPos,
      bearing,
    });

    // twilight threshold
    if (sunPos.altitude > -6) {
      visibleSunPositions.push({
        azimuth: sunPos.azimuth,
        altitude: sunPos.altitude,
        bearing,
      });
    }
  }
```

